 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jspuonti>JSPuonti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>In Brilliant Color <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/jspicon.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/02 9:57:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well, ONE way to do it..</span><hr size=1> The way I do that effect, when needed, is that I (obviously) first color and shade the image as normal. I take a copy of the finished image (select all, copy merged in Photoshop) and paste it into a new file, then take a copy of the lineart layer and paste it on another layer ontop of the colored one.<br>
<br>
I then make sure both layers are aligned (by &quot;flicking&quot; the top layer on and off to see that the lineart matches), and take the eraser tool. Depending on how I want the fade to happen, I then erase the lineart layer to reveal the colored layer beneath with a soft-edged eraser and use either a low opacity (10, 20%) or opacity-by-pen-pressure (pentools).<br>
<br>
Here's a picture:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.saunalahti.fi/jspuonti/colorfade.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
I can't be sure if this is the way that picture was done, but this method is a very, very simple way to get the same effect <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jspuonti>JSPuonti</A> at: 11/30/02 10:06:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=squashai>squashai</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://freehost19.websamba.com/squashai/junk/_ez-icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/02 4:29:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> And...</span><hr size=1> Another neat way is to use the selection lasso tool <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>instead</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of the eraser..<br>
<br>
Then, use the &quot;Feather&quot; option under the &quot;Selection&quot; menu. That will smooth the edges out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=spyders17>spyders17</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/02 5:03:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/p_air_art/zeratulblinksmall.txt WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And...</span><hr size=1> check into using layer masks they're really helpful<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.thinkdan.com/tutorials/photoshop/layermasks/">www.thinkdan.com/tutorial...ayermasks/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p>Spyders17<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.artprojectx.com"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/p_air_art/sitegfx/apxbanner.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Visit Art Project X, or your father dies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jspuonti>JSPuonti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>In Brilliant Color <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/jspicon.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/02 11:51:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> IMO..</span><hr size=1> The mask method is actually better than using the eraser, since you're not making any changes into actual image data and can hence un-do and change the fade at any time without needing to bringing in a &quot;fresh&quot; copy of the lineart layer.<br>
<br>
The lasso / feather technique is less flexible than the other two mentioned in this thread, since for every selection you can only set one feather range. So the &quot;fade&quot; you create is always the same size (happens over as many pixels).<br>
<br>
Using the eraser or mask methods allows you to make &quot;tighter&quot; transitions in some parts, and &quot;more loose&quot; transitions in others. To achieve this with the lasso tool you'd have to make several selections with different feather settings. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightyquest>MightyQUEST</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.s-a-w-s.com/quest/realm/triforce2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/02 1:40:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.s-a-w-s.com/quest/explosion2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMO..</span><hr size=1> If I were to GUESS, I'd say using a layer mask and a black-to-white gradient, since the line of gradient IS straight up and down.<br>
<br>
The mask would be on a layer of all the colors. (If you have multiple color layers: Make only the color's layer visible, make a new layer BELOW the lineart, [name it colors for visual purposes] select the new blank layer with the color layers active, and press ctrl-alt-shift-E [This makes all visible merge onto the layer, while keeping the layers your merging still existent, so you can alter them and re-merge onto the colors layer] then un-visible the seperate colors and make the BG and lineart and any effects visible again, leaving the &quot;colors&quot; layer visible.)<br>
<br>
Then it's just a simple matter of applying a layer mask with a gradient. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/bherosreality"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.s-a-w-s.com/quest/realm/hero'sreality-minibanner.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=4621.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=4621.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4621.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=4621.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=4621.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4621.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4621.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="